  "body": "Hello everyone!\r\n\r\nI'm new in the geth world, and i decided to create my first node for get faster transactions with metamask and use my node with a bot that is hosted on a gcp (remote rpc from my server), so i took a dedicated server (Ax101 from hetzner).\r\nI followed a youtube tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ftS-SlzCCn4&t=903s\r\nAnd with the help of the GitHub, i tried to open my http and ws server, so this is my systemctl file : \r\n\r\n```\r\n[Unit]\r\nDescription=Go Ethereum Client\r\nAfter=network.target\r\nWants=network.target\r\n[Service]\r\nUser=eth\r\nGroup=eth\r\nType=simple\r\nRestart=always\r\nRestartSec=5\r\nExecStart=geth --datadir /home/ether/chain/data --syncmode \"snap\" --cache=112640 --rpc.allow-unprotected-txs --txlookuplimit 0 --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.api eth,net,web3,txpool --metrics --maxpeers 100 --ws --http.corsdomain '*' --ws.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws.origins '*' --ws.api eth,net,web3,txpool,debug\r\n[Install]\r\nWantedBy=default.target\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy eth_syncing is good, and i follow the instructions from Geth Github my http and ws is open with defaults ports...\r\nBut when i want to bench my node with an python script i got these error :  \r\n\r\n```\r\nrequests.exceptions.ConnectionError: HTTPConnectionPool(host='XX.XX.XX.XXX', port=8000): Max retries exceeded with url: / (Caused by NewConnectionError('<urllib3.connection.HTTPConnection object at 0x0000029A8XXXXXXX>: Failed to establish a new connection\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy ports are opens because when i request `{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_syncing\",\"params\":[],\"id\":1}`  to my websocket i get a good response...\r\n\r\nAnd i don't understand why...\r\n\r\nIf someone can help me that's could be great, thanks...ðŸ¤",
